"{\"uid\": \"kswo.com-2024-06-21-oklahoma-city-tabbed-host-multiple-olympic-events-2028\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"OKLAHOMA CITY, Okla. (KSWO) - LA28, the plan behind the 2028 Olympics in Los Angeles announced an update to the master plan for venues including two events moving to OKC.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 170, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 73, \"end\": 84, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999928080093797, \"rank\": 7.017803207394945e-06, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 166, \"end\": 169, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma_City\", \"score\": 0.9999759462910637, \"rank\": 2.3977457299244547e-05, \"text\": \"OKC\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to the Olympics website, Oklahoma City will play host to softball and canoe slalom attributed to what the committee describes as \\\"world-class venues.\\\"\", \"from\": 172, \"to\": 332, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 207, \"end\": 215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma\", \"score\": 0.9975561837795789, \"rank\": 0.0019136807895974751, \"text\": \"Oklahoma\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics website states:  Both the existing canoe slalom and softball stadiums in Oklahoma City are built to international competition standards, and the local community has consistently supported top tournaments for both sports, ensuring a high-quality experience for both athletes and fans, while allowing LA28 to achieve cost savings and revenue gains to support its balanced budget.\", \"from\": 334, \"to\": 724, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 420, \"end\": 428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma\", \"score\": 0.9975561837795789, \"rank\": 0.0019136807895974751, \"text\": \"Oklahoma\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Currently, Oklahoma is the only state outside of California to host events in the 2028 games.\", \"from\": 726, \"to\": 819, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 737, \"end\": 745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma\", \"score\": 0.9975561837795789, \"rank\": 0.0019136807895974751, \"text\": \"Oklahoma\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma\"}, {\"begin\": 775, \"end\": 785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 0.9955638868144817, \"rank\": 0.004313706757024282, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright 2024 KSWO.\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 841, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 842, \"to\": 862, \"entities\": []}]}"